<chapter id="design_overview">

	<title>Design Overview</title>
	<para>&THIS.PLATFORM; &THIS.APPLICATION;
		provides the user with
		NIO
		like transport abstraction.
		User works with:
	</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Channel provider</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        Factory class that creates a concrete implementaion of the channel, that hides transport details.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Selector</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        Object that can be queried about state of channel I/O operations.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Selection key</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        Object encapsulating information about I/O ready channel.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Channel</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        Object handling I/O operation.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>M3UA Messages and Parameters</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        Objects representing specific metadata (such as SS7 protocol messages and M3UA management messages)
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
